---
title: Cancel Booking Flow With Authorization
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant TG as Telegram
    participant GW as bot-gateway
    participant Redis as Redis
    participant BK as booking-service
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant NOT as notification-service

    User->>TG: open my bookings
    TG->>GW: update
    GW->>Redis: duplicate update check
    GW->>BK: signed GET /bookings?telegramUserId=X
    Note over GW,BK: HMAC + replay protection + signed user id
    BK->>PG: read user's bookings
    BK-->>GW: bookings
    GW->>TG: show bookings

    User->>TG: confirm cancel
    TG->>GW: callback
    GW->>BK: signed PATCH /bookings/:id status cancelled
    BK->>PG: verify booking owner

    alt user owns booking
        BK->>PG: update booking status
        BK->>PG: write audit booking.cancelled
        BK->>Redis: publish stream:booking.cancelled
        Redis->>NOT: consume notification.send if needed
        NOT->>TG: send cancellation message
        BK-->>GW: cancelled booking
        GW->>TG: show success
    else user does not own booking
        BK->>PG: write audit booking.cancel.forbidden
        BK-->>GW: FORBIDDEN
        GW->>TG: show access denied
    end
